            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab>+ In Dei nomine. Regnante domno nostro Aistolfo rege, anno regni
                        eius quinto, per indictionem septima, mense iulio; feliciter. Dum per
                        iussionem domno excilentissimo <persName ref="#people/48"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Aistolf</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rege</rs> demandatum fuisset mihi <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/389">Alpert</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">duci</rs> seo et <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/320">Walprand</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs>
                        <rs key="#Commutatio">viganeum</rs> facere de res <persName
                            key="#Specialized_workers" ref="#people/390">Auripert</persName>
                        <rs key="#Specialized_workers">pictori</rs> cum <geogName key="#Curtes"
                            ref="#estates/78"><rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> domni <rs
                                key="#Emperor/king">regi</rs></geogName>, ita et factum est. Unde
                        duas cartulas uno tenore fuirunt conscriptas. Et dum per preceptum ipsius
                        domno nostro confermatus fieri devirent, requisivimus cartula illa quem de
                        partis <rs key="#Curtes #Emperor/king">curtis regia</rs> de ipso viganium
                        inn <rs key="#Mother_churches">eclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/68">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName> data fuera; minime ea iungere potuimus, eo quod in <rs
                            key="#Army">exercitus</rs> domno nostro peruerat. Et dum hec dictum
                        fuisset domno regi per <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/343"
                            >Peredeus</persName> vir beatissimus <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs>,
                        eo quod ipsa cartula minime invenire potuisset, demandavet ipse piissimo
                        domno regi, alia tale cartula relevare per ipso <rs key="#Notary"
                            >notario</rs>, qui ea antea scripserad, qualis ille erat, quem de parte
                        eclesie ad curtis regia emissat fuerad. Placuet adque convinet inter
                        eclesiam Sancti Martini nec non et curtes domni regi, et qualiter au ipso
                        piissimo et ad Deo conserbato domno Aistolf rege est demandatum, ut cambium
                        de curte ipsius <placeName ref="#places/4">Lucense</placeName> in predicta
                        eclesia Sancti Martini melioratum datum fieri devirent pro personas de
                        germanis vel germanas Auripert pictori seo et <rs key="#Work_and_workers"
                            >homenis</rs> pertinentibus eorum vel <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >res</rs> quem ad manum sua abuirunt, qui sunt pertenentes eclesie
                        sancti Martini. Unde consentientem vir beatissimus Walprand episcopus et au
                        ipso ordinati fuirunt da parte eclesie ipsa commutationem faciendum
                            <persName key="#Missus #Archpriests"><name ref="Iordanus"
                                >Iordanni</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archpriests">arcipresbitero</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Missus #Archdeacons"><name ref="Ragibertus"
                            >Rachipert</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archdeacons">arcidiaconus</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Other_minor_officer #Missus" ref="#people/391">Auduaci</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_minor_officer">scario</rs>; et da parte domni regi ab Alpert
                        duce ordinati fuirunt ad ipsa res extimandum <persName
                            key="#Other_minor_officer #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"
                            ref="#people/392">Teutpert</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_minor_officer">scario</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Teudebrandus"
                                >Teutprand</name></persName> filio quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Teudulus">Teuppoli</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Grasulus"
                                >Grasulus</name></persName> negudias. Unde constat dedisset eclesia
                        Sancti Martini: in primis, <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa
                            avitationis</rs> ipsius Auripert vel de germani eius una cum <rs
                            key="#Casalini/fundamenta">fundamenta</rs> sua hic infra <placeName
                            ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Casalini/fundamenta #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Inflow #Purchase"
                                ><rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs></placeName>; et recipet in viganei
                        locum a curte domni regi <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> cum
                            <rs key="#Casalini/fundamenta">fundamenta</rs> [sua hic] prope <rs
                            key="#Walls">muro</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Casalini/fundamenta #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Counter-gift"
                                ><rs key="#Cities">civitatis</rs></placeName>, ubi residerunt
                            <persName key="#Other_minor_officer" ref="#people/393"
                            >Aumundulo</persName> et <persName key="#Other_minor_officer"
                            ref="#people/394">Silvolus</persName>, <rs key="#Other_minor_officer"
                            >qui fuerunt epistolas deportantes</rs>; et pro <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> quem abuirunt Auripert vel de
                        germani eius ad area ubi ipse casella edificata est, recipet eclesia Sancti
                        Martini terra in atpretiato sub extimationem intra clausura illa prope muro
                        civitatis ubi ipse casella Aumunduli et Silvoli edificata est; et pro <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> quam abuirunt in loco
                            <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Cereals #Wine #Oil #Fiscal_property #Object #Inflow #Purchase"
                            ref="#places/704">Lupelia</placeName> et in <placeName ref="#places/325"
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Cereals #Wine #Oil #Fiscal_property #Object #Inflow #Purchase"
                            >Pumpiano</placeName> prope <rs key="#Churches">eclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/251">Sancti
                            Machari</orgName> cum <rs key="#Cereals">terris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Oil">olivitis</rs>, vel omnia quantum in
                        suprascriptas locas avire visis fuirunt, recipet eclesia Sancti Martini <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie"><name ref="Willulus"
                                >Willuli</name></persName> et <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie"
                            >casa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie"><name ref="Gairepertulus"
                                >Gaipertuli</name></persName> et <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie"><name ref="Filipertus"
                                >Filipert</name></persName> in loco [… <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Casalini/fundamenta #Landed_possessions #Cereals #Wine #Oil #Chestnuts #Acorns #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Counter-gift"
                            ref="#places/513">Tu]rre</placeName> cum <rs key="#Casalini/fundamenta"
                            >fundamentas</rs> suas, <rs key="#Landed_possessions #Cereals"
                            >terris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Oil">olivitis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Acorns">silvis</rs>, <rs key="#Chestnuts">castaneitis</rs>,
                        omnia et in omnibus ad ipsas suprascriptas casas pertenentes in integrum;
                            <rs key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Exceptive">excepto homenis de ipse
                            case et fondamenta eorum hic infra civitate</rs> et <rs>terre</rs> eorum
                        ultra <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs> Ausare, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Exceptive">quem a curte domni regi est
                            reserbatum</rs>. Et de terre qui fuirunt de suprascripte case da Turre,
                        qui sunt hic circa civitatem, recipet eclesia Sancti Martini per mensura pro
                        terre qui fuerant Auripert vel de germani eius, in primis <rs key="#Cereals"
                            >campo</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Size #Cereals #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Counter-gift"
                            >Fontanolas</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Size">modiorum sex et sistariorum octo</rs> pro <rs key="#Cereals"
                            >campo</rs> ipsius Auripert vel de germani eius, loco qui dicitur
                            <placeName
                            key="#Size #Cereals #Fiscal_property #Object #Inflow #Purchase">ad
                            Ausare</placeName>, quod est <rs key="#Size">modiorum sex</rs>;
                        similiter recipet <rs key="#Mother_churches">eclesia</rs> Sancti Martini
                        duas <rs key="#Petiae">petias de terra</rs> in loco <placeName
                            key="#Petiae #Size #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Counter-gift #Royal_slave"
                            >Roncho</placeName>, una qui fuet <persName key="#Royal_slave"><name
                                ref="Protestulus">Protestuli</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">serbo domni regi</rs> et illa alia ipsorum case
                        pertenentem de <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/316"><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Mention" ref="#places/513"
                            >Turrem</placeName></geogName>, qui ad ipsi hominis avitaturis in Turre
                        da <persName><name ref="Sassulus">Saxulo</name></persName> in <rs
                            key="#Commutatio #Fiscal_property #Mention #Inflow #Purchase"
                            >viganium</rs> obvinet, qui sunt inter ambas petias <rs key="#Size"
                            >sistariorum duas minus de quinque modiorum</rs> propter duas petias de
                        terra qui fuerant Auripert vel de germani eius in ipso loco <placeName
                            key="#Petiae #Size #Textual_occurrence #Object #Inflow #Purchase"
                            >Roncho</placeName>, quod sunt per mensura <rs key="#Size">quattuor
                            sistariorum minus de quinque modiorum</rs>; et de <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terre</rs> ipsorum homenis avitaturis in
                            <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Size #Fiscal_property #Object #Exceptive"
                            ref="#places/513">Turre</placeName>, hic circa civitate, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Exceptive">reserbatum est a curte domni
                            regi terra <rs key="#Size">scaffiliorum tris</rs>, qui est prope <rs
                                key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                            <persName><name ref="Sassulus">Saxuli</name></persName></rs>; et pro <rs
                            key="#Wine">vinea</rs> ipsius Auripert vel de germani eius <placeName
                            key="#Size #Wine #Fiscal_property #Object #Inflow #Purchase">ultra <rs
                                key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs> Ausere</placeName>, qui est per mensura
                            <rs key="#Size">modiloco uno</rs>, et recipet eclesia Sancti Martini de
                        ipsis suprascritptis homenis de Turre, in ipso loco <placeName
                            key="#Wine #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Counter-gift"
                            ref="#places/513">Turre</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs> prope <rs key="#Churches">eclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/252">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>, alio modiloco, sub extimationem. Et ipse edificia
                        Auripert seo de germani eius in atpretiato fuirunt amplius <rs key="#Value"
                            >valentem soledus quatragenta</rs>, et ipse edificias quem curtes hic
                        prope civitate dedet eclesie Sancti Martini, et qualiter placuet domno regi,
                        ut ipse viganium quem curtes regia dare amplius valentem melioratus super
                        ipsum cambium quem ad eclesiam Sancti Martini reciperat, soledus
                        quatragenta; et de ipsa terra quem dedet curte regia relicum fuet <rs
                            key="#Size">sistariorum quattuordeci</rs> tam pro ipsa meliorationem
                        quam et pro ipsas fabricas que amplius fuet valentem. Omnia adimplivet
                        curtis domni regi eclesie Sancti Martini de fondamento et clausura illa ubi
                        ipse casa ipsorum Aumunduli et Sivoli edificata est, cum <rs
                            key="#Fruits/vegetables">pomis</rs> vel omnia ipsa clausura in integrum,
                        excepto res movile. De <rs key="#Slave_labour">hominis</rs> viro dedet <rs
                            key="#Mother_churches">eclesia</rs> Sancti Martini: <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Inflow #Purchase #Slave_labour"><persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Ansebrandus"
                                >Ansprand</name></persName>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name
                                    ref="Catocciulus">Catocciulo</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Fusculus">Fosculo</name></persName>,
                                <persName key="#Slave_labour #Other_clerics"><name ref="Emmulus"
                                    >Hemmulo</name></persName>
                            <rs key="#Other_clerics">clerico</rs>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"
                                    ><name ref="Teulus">Teulo</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Mauriculus"
                                >Mauriculo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name
                                    ref="Aurifia">Aurifia</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Auriperga"
                                >Auriperga</name></persName>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name
                                    ref="Castaldus">Castaldu</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour">[…lo]</persName> et <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Auricundula"
                                >Aricondula</name></persName></rs>; et recipet a <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >curte</rs> domni <rs key="#Emperor/king">regi</rs>: <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Counter-gift #Slave_labour"
                                ><persName key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Mauripertus"
                                    >Mauripert</name></persName>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"
                                    ><name ref="Baroncellus">Baroncello</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Bonari">Bonari</name></persName>,
                                <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Agibrandus"
                                >Agiprand</name></persName>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name
                                    ref="Lucibrandus">Luciprand</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Audibertus"
                                >Audipert</name></persName> et <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name
                                    ref="Maginperga">Magniperga</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Ermetruda"
                                >Ermitroda</name></persName>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name
                                    ref="Ciontula">Ciontula</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Maurella">Maurella</name></persName>
                            et <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Ansperta"
                                >Asperta</name></persName>, <persName key="#Slave_labour"><name
                                    ref="Sigebertus">Seipert</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour"><name ref="Teudebertus"
                                >Teudipert</name></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Slave_labour #Other_clerics"><name ref="Ildebertus"
                                    >Hildipert</name></persName>
                            <rs key="#Other_clerics">clerico</rs> et <persName key="#Slave_labour"
                                    ><name ref="Gaitroda">Gaitroda</name></persName></rs>. Modo viro
                        qualiter ipse cambium ex urtaque partis factum vel contraditum est,
                        stavilitum diveat permanire, qualiter suprascriptua commutatio acta est per
                        Walprand episcopus et Alpert duce. Unde duas cartulas uno tenure conscriptas
                            <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Radalbertus"
                            >Radalpert</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notario</rs> scrivere commonuemus. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/4">Luca</placeName>, regnum et indictionem suprascripta;
                        feliciter. Cartula ista relevata est per demandationem ipsius domno nostro
                        Aistolf <rs key="#Emperor/king">regi</rs> inn anno septimo, indictione nona,
                        mense septembrio. + Ego Alpert dux in anc cartula commutationis a me facta
                        et Walprando episcopo, sicut supra legitur, propria manu mea scuscripsi. +
                        Ego Teutprand, qui in hanc cummutationem interfuit ad ipsam res extimandum,
                        manus mea suscripsi. Signum + manus <persName
                            key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name ref="Alateus"
                                >Alatei</name></persName> filio quondam <persName><name ref="Alahis"
                                >Alais</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis. + Ego <persName
                            key="#Witness #Priests"><name ref="Teuderadus"
                            >Teuderadu</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> in ach cartula comutationis facta a
                        Gualprandu episcopus et Alpertu duce propria manus mea me teste supcripsi. +
                        Ego <persName key="#Witness #Priests"><name ref="Filosofronius"
                                >Filosofronius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> in hanc cartula cummutationis facta a
                        Gualprand episcopus et Alpert dux propria manus mea testis subscripsi. + Ego
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Gairepertus"
                            >Gairipert</name></persName> i hanc cartula cummutationis facta ad
                        Walprand episcopus et Alpert dux, sicot superius legitor, me teste
                        supiscripsi. + Ego <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Sintrualdus"
                                >Suintrualdus</name></persName> in hanc cartula cummutationis facta
                        ad Walprandus episcopus seo Alpertu dux, sicut superius legetur, me tesstes
                        subscripsi. + Ego Radalpert, qui hanc cartula relevavi per
                        demandamandationem ipsius domno nostro regi per dicto Alpert doci, et
                        qualiter ipsius demadatio fuet, conplivi et dedi. </ab>
                        </div>
